5.notes:
This template transmits the study data to a compatible server-side backend. Currently, it supports the PHP, Open Lab and JATOS backends.

It will wait until the data is transferred, showing a waiting screen with the text defined below, and continue with the remainder of the study after the transmission is complete. Please note that this screen will be skipped if no compatible backend is available.

content.text:
In this task, you will complete 1 block with 200 trials.

In each trial, you will see a 3 by 3 letter grid:

In this kind of experiment, it is 
very important to have a controlled environment.

Therefore, we would like to ask you to perform this experiment 
in a quiet room without distractions. Please set this website to full screen 
mode and close all programs on your computer and tabs in your 
internet browser. Please also move your mouse 
cursor off the screen.

Please do not run any music in the background. However, we ask you 
to enable sound on your computer.

Next, we will provide some instructions regarding the task.

Press the spacebar to continue.

Your task is to identify as fast and as accurately as possible
whether the center letter (i.e., the letter in the middle) belongs to the "A" or "H"
category. You will learn more about the two categories shortly.

For instance, in the scenario below the center letter belongs
to the "A" category. This means that the correct response in this trial would be "A".

Importantly, in each trial the center letter and the background letters will change.

However, your task is to focus solely on the center letter and to ignore the 
letters surrounding it. Perform the task as fast and as accurately as possible.

Press the spacebar to continue.

Place your fingers on the "A" and "H" letter on the keyboard,
then press the spacebar to begin the block.

content.text:
If you think the center letter belongs to the "A" category, press the "A" key.
If you think the center letter belongs to the "H" category, press the "H" key.

We now start the real experiment. 

Remember: only judge the category of the center letter and try to 
ignore the neighboring letters. In each trial, answer the question 'does the 
center letter belong to the 'A' or 'H' category?'.

Press the spacebar to continue.

Thank you for participating in this experiment.

The experiment will consist of one task with 200 trials.
The task will take around 10-15 minutes to complete. 

Press the spacebar to continue.

content.text:
The aim of the first warm-up block is to familiarize you with
the different levels of the center letter. For this reason, you will
initially only see and judge one letter, that is, the center letter.

Press the spacebar to continue.

This was the first warm-up.

Press the spacebar to continue with the second warm-up block.

Here you see all levels of the center letter at once. 

The upper four letters belong to the "H" category.

The lower four letters belong to the "A" category.

Press the spacebar to continue.
